<br>
Determination kind of degrades the most obvious effects of Purge... Kind of redundent to spend Realm Points on a passive ability that decreases stun and mezz time as well as spend more on another ability that negates those all together on activation... So if you get Purge just for stuns or Mezz's, it seems kind of useless if you build Determination up to a level higher than 3, but that's my opinion... That is, unless you are wanting at least 'some' defense from stun/mezz's at ALL times, because sometimes you'll find yourself in a situation where Purge isn't avaliable to get rid of them... In that case, get purge and put Determination to level 3... If you find yourself with Realm Ability points left over, raise it up some more if you want...<br>
<br>
If you're a quick race, work on dodger a few levels... It noticably increases your evade by far, and if you're thrust work on dodger anyways... That level 50 thrust evade stun is pretty useful at times (Although you'll be stunning a ton with the Hypnotic Darkness parry style, but who says you can stun 'too' much?)<br>
<br>
If you are specced 50/50 in dual and your weapon, working on Mastery of Parrying a few levels would help you be more defensive... AND it's built off of dexterity so you can build up Mastery of Pain with it as well, and Mastery of Pain speaks for itself... Max it out and your damage will skyrocket...<br>
<br>
Let's not forget Tireless... One train in it is worthwhile...<br>
<br>
All in all, save a few points back until after the Realm Ability Review that Mythic is conducting... Chances are, some Realm Abilities we wouldn't plan on using may prove useful, although I'm sure they will be giving out full realm ability respecs when those details hit IF anything gets changed...<br>
<br>
These are my suggestions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>Vith<br>
