Talifer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=uhno>uhno</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.grumbled.com/images/paradoxicon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#000000>(7/24/03 8:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=293.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wondering if ....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>At 50+16 if I'm adding it right you have a 58% chance to double swing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
DW does not have a hard cap and no evidence exists to suggest overspeccing does not have the full effect. There is also no evidence to support that it does give the full effect. <br>
<br>
Since offhand swings are sometimes erratic and random at best it is impossible to get accurate data either way. Only Mythic could ever truly answer and they haven't chosen to. <br>
<br>
Your formula for determining chance to swing offhand is a little off.<br>
The accepted formula to swing offhand I have always seen referred to is:<br>
DW % = 25% + (level/4) + (spec/2) + (DRlevel*3)<br>
<br>
At 50 and +16 the chance would be 25% + 12.5% + 33% or 70%.<br>
<br>
Adding duelists reflexes is 3% chance per level. so at DR2 your offhand chance with this makeup should be 76%.<br>
<br>
Theoretically at RR10 with 50 in DW and duelists reflexes 5 you should be at 88% chance to swing your offhand.<br>
